<div class="container">
    <header>
        <h1>IOTA Notarization</h1>
        <p>Understanding Document Immutability &amp; Version Tracking for VeriPura</p>
    </header>

    <div class="content">
        <section id="introduction">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>IOTA Notarization provides two distinct approaches for document verification in supply chain compliance:</p>

            <div class="approach-box">
                <h3><span class="badge badge-immutable">IMMUTABLE</span> Standard Notarization</h3>
                <p><strong>How it works:</strong> Document is hashed and notarized once, creating a permanent timestamp proving the document existed in that exact state at that specific moment. Any change creates a different hash.</p>
                <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Final signed certificates, approved regulatory documents, lab test results</p>
            </div>

            <div class="approach-box">
                <h3><span class="badge badge-versioned">VERSIONED</span> Change-Tracked Notarization</h3>
                <p><strong>How it works:</strong> Each version of a document is notarized with links to previous versions, creating an auditable chain showing what changed, when, and by whom.</p>
                <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Draft documents, multi-stage approvals, collaborative workflows, amended certificates</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="use-cases">
            <h2>VeriPura Use Cases Illustrated</h2>

            <div class="use-case">
                <h3>Use Case 1: Certificate Amendment Tracking <span class="badge badge-versioned">VERSIONED</span></h3>
                <p><strong>Scenario:</strong> A health certificate is issued, but the exporter discovers a typo in the product description. The health authority issues an amendment.</p>

                <div class="version-chain">
                    <div class="version-item">
                        <strong>Version 1 (Original)</strong><br>
                        Issued: Jan 15, 2026<br>
                        Product: "Frozen shrimp"<br>
                        Hash: abc123...<br>
                        Status: "Issued"
                    </div>
                    <div class="version-item">
                        <strong>Version 2 (Amended)</strong><br>
                        Issued: Jan 17, 2026<br>
                        Product: "Frozen prawns" (corrected)<br>
                        Hash: def456...<br>
                        Previous: abc123...<br>
                        Change: "Product name correction - no material change"<br>
                        Status: "Amended"
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h4>VeriPura Benefits:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Verifies amendment was authorized by proper authority</li>
                    <li>Distinguishes minor corrections from fraud attempts</li>
                    <li>Alerts importer to review changes</li>
                    <li>Provides complete audit trail for EU customs</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="use-case">
                <h3>Use Case 2: Multi-Stage Approval Workflow <span class="badge badge-versioned">VERSIONED</span></h3>
                <p><strong>Scenario:</strong> A certificate requires sequential approvals from multiple authorities, each potentially requesting changes.</p>

                <div class="version-chain">
                    <div class="version-item"><strong>v1:</strong> Exporter submits draft → notarized</div>
                    <div class="version-item"><strong>v2:</strong> Health inspector requests pesticide test → "Pending - test required"</div>
                    <div class="version-item"><strong>v3:</strong> Lab results added → "Test results attached"</div>
                    <div class="version-item"><strong>v4:</strong> Health authority approves → "Final - approved"</div>
                    <div class="version-item"><strong>v5:</strong> Chamber of commerce co-signs → "Certified for export"</div>
                </div>

                <h4>VeriPura Benefits:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Tracks workflow progress in real-time</li>
                    <li>Ensures no approval steps are skipped</li>
                    <li>Smart contract enforcement of proper sequence</li>
                    <li>Only marks "export-ready" when all approvals complete</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="use-case">
                <h3>Use Case 3: Immutable Lab Test Results <span class="badge badge-immutable">IMMUTABLE</span></h3>
                <p><strong>Scenario:</strong> A laboratory conducts pesticide residue testing on a produce shipment. Results must be timestamped and unchangeable.</p>

                <h4>Implementation:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Lab completes test and generates PDF report</li>
                    <li>Report is immediately hashed and notarized to IOTA</li>
                    <li>Timestamp proves test wasn't backdated</li>
                    <li>Any alteration to report creates different hash (detected immediately)</li>
                </ul>

                <h4>VeriPura Benefits:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Prevents result tampering or backdating</li>
                    <li>Automatically verifies test is &lt;30 days old (EU requirement)</li>
                    <li>Customs can verify authenticity without contacting lab</li>
                    <li>Protects labs from false fraud accusations</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="use-case">
                <h3>Use Case 4: Recurring Shipment Templates <span class="badge badge-versioned">VERSIONED</span></h3>
                <p><strong>Scenario:</strong> An exporter ships mangoes weekly to the same importer. Most certificate details remain constant, only batch-specific information changes.</p>

                <div class="version-chain">
                    <div class="version-item">
                        <strong>Master Template (Immutable):</strong><br>
                        Exporter details, Importer details, Product specs, Treatment protocols<br>
                        Hash: master_abc123...
                    </div>
                    <div class="version-item">
                        <strong>Batch Instance 1 (Jan 20):</strong><br>
                        References: master_abc123...<br>
                        Batch: #2026-003, Harvest: Jan 18, Qty: 5,000 kg<br>
                        Hash: batch_001_def...
                    </div>
                    <div class="version-item">
                        <strong>Batch Instance 2 (Jan 27):</strong><br>
                        References: master_abc123...<br>
                        Batch: #2026-004, Harvest: Jan 25, Qty: 4,800 kg<br>
                        Hash: batch_002_ghi...
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h4>VeriPura Benefits:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Reduces redundant data entry for repeat shipments</li>
                    <li>Maintains consistency across all shipments</li>
                    <li>Easy comparison (only batch-specific fields vary)</li>
                    <li>If master template updates, all future instances reference new version</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="quiz">
            <h2>Knowledge Check Quiz</h2>
            <div class="quiz-section">
                <form id="quizForm">
                    <div class="question">
                        <h3>Question 1</h3>
                        <p>A laboratory has completed pesticide residue testing on a produce shipment and needs to
